<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>William Held</title>
  <link rel="icon" href="images/favicon.png">
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Raleway:400,300,600" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/skeleton/2.0.4/skeleton.min.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/4.7.0/css/font-awesome.min.css">
  <style>
    body { font-family: 'Raleway', sans-serif; color: #222; }
    h4 { letter-spacing: .1rem; text-transform: uppercase; }
    .header { margin-top: 60px; margin-bottom: 60px; }
    .paper { margin-bottom: 20px; line-height: 1.2; }
    .paper p { margin-bottom: 2px; }
    .paper-buttons { margin-top: 2px; }
    .paper .button { display: inline-block; height: 20px; padding: 0 5px; font-weight: 100; line-height: 20px; margin-bottom: 0; text-transform: none; }
    .docs-section { border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding: 4rem 0; }
    .scroll-container { overflow-x: auto; white-space: nowrap; padding-bottom: 10px; }
    .scroll-container .paper { display: inline-block; margin-right: 10px; vertical-align: top; }
    footer { text-align: center; color: rgba(0,0,0,0.4); border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding: 15px 0 40px; }
    .profile-pic {
      border-radius: 50%;
      width: 150px;
      height: 150px;
      object-fit: cover;
      overflow-clip-margin: unset;
    }
    .main-description h1,
    .main-description h2,
    .main-description h3,
    .main-description h4,
    .main-description h5,
    .main-description h6,
    .main-description h7,
    .main-description p {
      margin: 0 0 1rem;
      line-height: 1.25;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <section class="header">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="three columns">
          <img class="u-max-full-width profile-pic" src="images/profile.jpeg" alt="Profile">
        </div>
        <div class="nine columns main-description">
          <h2>William Held</h1>
          <h5>PhD Student at Georgia Tech, Visiting Researcher at Stanford</h5>
          <h6>held@stanford.edu</h6>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="twelve columns main-description">
          <h4>Bio</h2>
          <p>I am currently a PhD student in Machine Learning at Georgia Tech, advised by Prof. <a href="https://cs.stanford.edu/~diyiy/">Diyi Yang</a>, and a visiting researcher at the Stanford NLP Group. During my PhD, I have interned at Google AI working on Google Assistant and at Meta GenAI on pretraining for Llama 3 and 4.</p>
          <p>My research develops methods to improve the robustness and fairness of language technology across domains and modalities. The goal of my research is to make fundamental language technologies more robust and easier to adapt, so that it can be the foundation of innovation by a broader and more diverse pool of innovators. During my PhD, I have worked on the following topics:</p>
          <h6>Language, Dialect, and Domain Robustness</h6>
          <p>Developing methods to quickly adapt language technology to new &amp; diverse settings with little to no additional training data.
          <br/>
          [(<a href="https://aclanthology.org/2023.findings-acl.51/">ACL 2023a</a>), (<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2501.11747">Meta 2025</a>)]</p>
          <h6>Social &amp; Cultural Factors in NLP</h6>
          <p>Understanding how human social systems inform and influence the performance of language technology for different user groups.
          <br/>
          [(<a href="https://aclanthology.org/2024.acl-long.853/">ACL 2024a</a>), (<a href="https://aclanthology.org/2024.findings-acl.241/">ACL 2024b</a>)]</p>
          <h6>Speech Processing &amp; Voice Assistants</h6>
<p>Evaluating and improving the ability for language models to assist users naturally and efficiently through spoken conversation.
          <br/>
          [(<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2410.02678">ACL 2025a</a>), (<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2502.15919">ACL 2025b</a>)]</p>
          <p>Before my Phd, I was an engineer at <a href="https://techcrunch.com/2020/11/18/marissa-mayers-startup-launches-its-first-official-product-sunshine-contacts/">Sunshine AI</a> where I reported directly to <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/marissamayer/">Marissa Mayer</a> and performed research with Prof. <a href="https://web.stanford.edu/~jurafsky/">Dan Jurafsky</a>. I did my undergraduate degree at NYU Abu Dhabi, where I worked on lexical semantics and Arabic NLP advised by Prof. <a href="https://nyuad.nyu.edu/en/academics/divisions/science/faculty/nizar-habash.html">Nizar Habash</a>.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="row">
      <div class="six columns">
        <h5>General Links</h5>
        <ul>
          <li><a rel="me" href="https://www.threads.net/@william.held">Bluesky</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://twitter.com/WilliamBarrHeld">Twitter</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/williambarrheld/">LinkedIn</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://github.com/Helw150">Github</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="six columns">
        <h5>Academic Links</h5>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="files/res.pdf">Resume</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/William-B.-Held/46552910">Semantic Scholar</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=SP9VJNkAAAAJ&amp;hl=en">Google Scholar</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://dblp.org/pid/245/8601.html">DBLP</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  {% if notebooks or apps %}
  <div class="container docs-section">
    <div class="row">
      {% if notebooks %}
      <div class="six columns">
        <h4>Notebooks</h4>
        <div class="scroll-container">
          {% for notebook in notebooks %}
          <!-- {{ notebook.display_name }} Notebook -->
          <div class="paper">
            <p class="title">{{ notebook.display_name }}</p>
            <div class="paper-buttons">
              <a href="{{ notebook.html_path }}" class="button">Open Notebook</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          {% endfor %}
        </div>
      </div>
      {% endif %}

      {% if apps %}
      <div class="six columns">
        <h4>Apps</h4>
        <div class="scroll-container">
          {% for app in apps %}
          <!-- {{ app.display_name }} App -->
          <div class="paper">
            <p class="title">{{ app.display_name }}</p>
            <div class="paper-buttons">
              <a href="{{ app.html_path }}" class="button">Open App</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          {% endfor %}
        </div>
      </div>
      {% endif %}
    </div>
  </div>
  {% endif %}

